725751f-b.title: Queens: 98th Street - Jamaica Avenue
725751f-b.text:
98th Street (formerly Diamond Street), west side, north of
Jamaica Ave., showing in a set of two views the John B. Napier
farmhouse of 1860. J. Napier was the owner in 1891. The first
Napier settled here in 1844 and died in 1890. ''At a meeting of
the inhabitants of Woodville, held in August 1853, Dominicus;
Vandeveer being chairman, the name was changed to 'Woodhaven.'
August 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
